1
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,040
But I look out for you brothers,

2
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,320
so shouldn't you brothers cut me some slack too?

3
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:44,240
I actually know what you want to say.

4
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:46,040
But this time it's different.

5
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:48,840
Dayazhai is the major shareholder.

6
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:50,280
They call the shots.

7
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,200
As for me,

8
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:54,520
I'm just riding on their coattails.

9
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:56,240
At best, I only get the leftovers.

10
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:58,720
Here's the thing.

11
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:01,960
Today's a good day.

12
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:03,160
Bro Min is here.

13
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,080
Let me raise a toast.

14
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:06,720
I'll down a big one.

15
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:08,520
Here goes.

16
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:12,160
With some liquid courage,

17
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,640
let me share a few heartfelt words with Bro Min.

18
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:16,640
Look, Bro Min,

19
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:19,560
you've led our association for over ten years.

20
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:20,840
Honestly speaking,

21
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:23,480
we all respect you wholeheartedly.

22
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:24,760
Why?

23
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,960
Because he's always thinking about us.

24
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:29,440
As long as you eat, we won't go hungry.

25
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,520
Isn't that right?

26
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,480
Right, right, right.

27
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,560
That's exactly how it is.

28
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:35,160
And this cultural creative project,

29
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,200
I've brought it up with you several times.

30
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,200
But you've never given a clear answer.

31
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:44,000
We brothers are really at our wits' end.

32
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:46,280
This cultural creative ship,

33
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:48,160
we absolutely have to board it.

34
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,280
If we can make it this time,

35
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,640
then we're set.

36
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:53,160
If we can't make it,

37
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:56,200
we truly won't get a better chance.

38
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:57,520
Well said.

39
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,000
Exactly.

40
00:02:58,920 --> 00:02:59,840
Yeah, Bro Min.

41
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,560
So, Bro Min,

42
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,160
figure something out.

43
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:06,120
Give your brothers a hand.

44
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,440
No matter when,

45
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:09,200
we brothers will always back you.

46
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:09,720
Right?

47
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:10,800
Come, a toast to Bro Min.

48
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:11,720
I'll drink up.

49
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:12,800
I'll down a big one. Here.

50
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:14,440
We'll definitely back Bro Min.

51
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:16,160
We'll keep backing him as chairman, right?

52
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:16,640
Right.

53
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,320
Bro Min, just help us out.

54
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:19,520
Yeah, please help us out.

55
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,360
We'll vote you in as chairman again.

56
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,280
Yeah, Bro Min, just help us out.

57
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:23,920
Okay, Bro Min?

58
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:26,880
Old Ren,

59
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:28,760
those are truly heartfelt words.

60
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,520
Sit, sit, sit.

61
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,320
Thank you.

62
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,200
Thanks to my brothers all these years

63
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:35,560
for always backing me up.

64
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:37,280
Without your support,

65
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:38,960
being chairman

66
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:40,760
wouldn't be easy.

67
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:46,480
But I've laid out the actual situation.

68
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:48,600
Whatever I can do for you brothers,

69
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:49,640
I'll do my very best.

70
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,200
What I can't help with,

71
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:53,240
I hope you won't force it.

72
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,040
Let me toast you as well.

73
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:03,240
I hope you can understand

74
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:05,080
and bear with me.

75
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:24,800
Bro Min

76
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,080
What kind of chairman are you?

77
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:28,360
All these years,

78
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,800
you don't even have one close brother.

79
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,800
As for close brothers,

80
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,120
having just you is enough.

81
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:36,240
That's plenty.

82
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,480
Why would I need more?

83
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,200
So tell me,

84
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,640
what's really going on?

85
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,240
I can't lead them

86
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,240
into making money from cultural products.

87
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:48,120
Whoever can lead them to profits,

88
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,080
that's who they'll follow.

89
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:51,120
Whoever pays the piper calls the tune.

90
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,520
That's perfectly normal.

91
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,080
Setting up

92
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,920
a trap for me right now,

93
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,760
it's just to give me a warning,

94
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,400
to lay their cards on the table.

95
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,400
Tell me the truth,

96
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,320
what you really feel.

97
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,960
Are you unwilling to give up being chairman?

98
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:13,360
It's not like it comes with a gun or any real power.

99
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,680
What's there to hold onto about being chairman?

100
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:16,240
People's hearts,

101
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:18,480
you can't warm them up,

102
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:20,800
and you can't keep them together.

103
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,440
Benevolence and morality, in the face of profit,

104
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,320
are less useful than a door curtain against the wind.

105
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,640
It's normal for businessmen to chase profits.

106
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,080
As chairman,

107
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:38,560
you can't just talk about brotherly loyalty.

108
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,360
You also have to think about

109
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,640
making sure everyone can put food on the table.

110
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,200
These past few years,

111
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,960
the Xuan paper businesses in our town have had it rough.

112
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:48,520
Several of them have been hovering on the brink of collapse.

113
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:50,440
Luckily,

114
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,120
Wannianhong

115
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:54,560
and the wallpaper industry have kept things afloat.

116
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:56,440
Just getting by isn't enough.

117
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,200
You need to find more ways

118
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,080
to help everyone prosper together.

119
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:00,880
That's the right thing to do.

120
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:02,880
I'll definitely help,

121
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:04,920
but if this keeps up,

122
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,760
I'm afraid I won't be up to the task.

123
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:09,440
So there you go,

124
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:12,720
that's why you came to me, right?

125
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,280
I came to have a heart-to-heart.

126
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:16,440
Fishing?

127
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:20,040
So this is your version of

128
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:22,000
"A willing fish takes the bait."

129
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:22,760
Got one! Got one!

130
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,360
Got it!

131
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:25,040
This one's big!

132
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,200
It's a big one!

133
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:27,760
Slow down, slow down, slow down.

134
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,040
This fish...

135
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,680
how did you hook it again?

136
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,280
Yeah.

137
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,160
You're playing me here.

138
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:34,680
Bro.

139
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:36,360
Alright, alright, alright.

140
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:46,760
This kills bacteria.

141
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:48,680
No thanks.

142
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:53,880
What young person eats garlic?

143
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:55,000
Only us old-timers eat it.

144
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:56,920
Come on, get to the point.

145
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,000
Me?

146
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,560
Just give me a straight answer.

147
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:03,920
If you're in, let's talk business.

148
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,360
If you're out,

149
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,800
then it's just us old-timers left,

150
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:12,080
holding on as long as we can.

151
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,440
I'm in.

152
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:18,920
Great!

153
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,000
Have some chicken soup.

154
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,440
Your mom made it.

155
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,120
It's great, fresh chicken.

156
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,880
Wait, wait, Dad, Dad.

157
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,120
Hold on, hold on a second.

158
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:30,720
If I'm in, I call the shots.

159
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,480
A thousand years of Xuan paper and the Xuan family.

160
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,320
We can't keep going down the old road.

161
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,840
It won't work anymore.

162
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:41,440
Songhezhai restructured their business.

163
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,520
Our orders have shrunk a lot.

164
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:46,000
All that backlog in the warehouse before,

165
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:48,280
all those piled-up paper stocks,

166
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,760
I finally managed to sell them off.

167
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,200
And how long has it been?

168
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,200
Now we've got backlog again.

169
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:54,840
We need

170
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:58,800
to change our marketing strategy.

171
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:00,840
Keep only one vat running,

172
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:03,360
still scooping authentic Xuan paper,

173
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:05,000
making it the best way possible.

174
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,200
Shift production.

175
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:09,280
Take on cultural merchandise orders.

176
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,560
Use cultural products to sustain Xuan paper.

177
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:14,280
Only then can we turn a profit.

178
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:17,560
That's how we turn things around.

179
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,320
That's one way to do it.

180
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,680
Constantly losing money,

181
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,640
the Xuan family wouldn't have made it this far.

182
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,400
We paper makers

183
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,560
have to eat too, right?

184
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,280
That makes sense.

185
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,920
But those old masters,

186
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,640
if they're not scooping paper,

187
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,120
that cultural creative work,

188
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:37,360
they'd have to learn it from scratch, right?

189
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:41,679
You said only one vat left.

190
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:43,880
That means

191
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,760
all the rest of the workers

192
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,440
have to be moved

193
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:49,440
to do that cultural creative stuff of yours.

194
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:52,880
Will they be willing?

195
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:55,400
Especially those old masters.

196
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:58,560
They've been with the Xuan family for years.

197
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,920
It's not all about money for them.

198
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:06,680
But this is the best idea your son could come up with

199
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:07,520
at the moment.

200
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:09,480
There's no other choice.

201
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,200
To sum it up,

202
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,480
we walk on two legs.

203
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,920
For the factory's long-term growth,

204
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,520
and so everyone can put food on the table.

205
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,640
But rest assured, everyone,

206
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:23,760
wages won't be cut.

207
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,560
Whether you keep making paper

208
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:28,000
or move into cultural creative work,

209
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,880
we Xuans won't shortchange anyone.

210
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,120
As for wages,

211
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:35,120
they'll only go up, never down.

212
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:37,400
So don't you worry.

213
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:48,360
Here's the thing.

214
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:51,360
The reason I called everyone here

215
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:52,840
is to discuss this with you all.

216
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:55,760
Just say what's on your mind.

217
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:56,680
Right.

218
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:00,800
My sister does cultural products at Dayazhai.

219
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,920
She only makes three or four thousand a month.

220
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:05,960
So what I'm saying is,

221
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,360
even if some of our masters switch roles,

222
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,600
Xuan Yan won't cut anyone's wages.

223
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:11,600
Don't worry.

224
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:14,040
That's not what I meant, Sis Xiumei.

225
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:17,000
We make six or seven thousand a month drying paper.

226
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,640
We earn it with a clear conscience,

227
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,120
and spend it without any guilt.

228
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,840
But for cultural products like yours,

229
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:24,400
hiring a worker for three or four thousand is enough.

230
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,600
That's a difference of several thousand.

231
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,800
Even if you're willing to pay,

232
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,280
we'd feel awkward taking it.

233
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:32,600
Auntie Sulan,

234
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,280
you're not looking at it right.

235
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:36,160
Think about it, once this factory grows,

236
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,280
and you become a manager,

237
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:38,360
you won't have to lift a finger,

238
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,240
and you'll earn even more than this.

239
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,600
That's the future.

240
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,200
The present is the present.

241
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,040
Everyone, speak up.

242
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,120
Say whatever's on your mind.

243
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,280
As for this factory,

244
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,960
it's now being handed over to Xuan Yan.

245
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,000
But I'm not going anywhere.

246
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,360
I'll look out for all of you.

247
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,520
No one's going to get a raw deal.

248
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,640
Right, um...

249
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,400
Magan, Xiao Yu.

250
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:23,840
You two speak up too.

251
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,640
Don't let me take office

252
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:26,760
with a label already slapped on me

253
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:28,280
saying I've mistreated everyone.

254
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:37,360
New leader, new direction, right?

255
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:39,080
Two big things coming at once.

256
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:41,280
So I think everyone should think it over carefully.

257
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:42,000
Right?

258
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,040
Give it some real thought.

259
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,480
Alright, alright.

260
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:58,760
Take some time to think and consider.

261
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,280
Once you've made up your minds,

262
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,600
we'll talk again.

263
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:03,160
Okay?

264
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:03,840
Sure, sure.

265
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:04,960
We'll get back to work then.

266
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:05,880
Alright.

267
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:06,440
Let's go.

268
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:08,040
Why are you standing there like a log?

269
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:11,280
Go on.

270
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:13,200
So... everyone give it some thought first.

271
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:15,600
I hope when we meet in a couple of days,

272
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:17,520
some of you will volunteer to step up

273
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:18,520
and join the cultural creative side.

274
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:19,800
Consider it doing me a favor.

275
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,480
Sure, sure.

276
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:22,520
Thank you.

277
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:49,200
Looking at this situation,

278
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,600
don't rush to decide.

279
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,520
Give everyone some time

280
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,760
to think it over, take it slow.

281
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:04,000
"Seeing the princess steal the arrow,

282
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,040
fills my heart with joy.

283
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:09,240
Standing at the palace gate,

284
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:10,760
calling out..."

285
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:12,240
You're up.

286
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:14,840
Go on.

287
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:15,840
Xiao Yu.

288
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:17,200
What are you thinking?

289
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:18,760
What? What?

290
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:20,840
I mean, what are your plans?

291
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:21,840
Me?

292
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:23,960
What plans could I have?

293
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:24,920
My plan is,

294
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:26,600
you two, as a couple,

295
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,640
can't just count on me, right?

296
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:29,440
Right?

297
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:31,640
Look, you know my family's situation.

298
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:33,000
You both know it.

299
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,760
I've got elders and kids to care for.

300
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:37,080
Honestly speaking,

301
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:39,400
I don't even know how long I'll keep drying paper,

302
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,040
and you want me to do cultural creative stuff?

303
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:42,840
What cultural creative work could I possibly do?

304
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,360
I've got an idea.

305
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:48,760
Spit it out already.

306
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:49,800
What idea? Tell us.

307
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:54,600
Come on, say it.

308
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:56,160
Move the paper, hurry.

309
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:56,800
Come on, quick, quick, quick.

310
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:57,480
Move it.

311
00:13:58,880 --> 00:13:59,840
What are you talking about?

312
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,760
Keeping it from me too?

313
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:03,520
It's nothing.

314
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:06,000
Xiao Yu says he wants to learn crosstalk.

315
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,480
Yeah, me.

316
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:08,400
Yes, yes.

317
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:12,200
So, as the saying goes,

318
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:15,120
"The blessed never need to worry,

319
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:16,840
while the unlucky toil themselves to death."

320
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:19,360
When you're old, the Xuan family will care for you.

321
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:21,000
We don't have your good fortune.

322
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,360
It's truly enviable.

323
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:23,800
Off we go.

324
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:30,400
Coming to this point,

325
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,880
who wouldn't feel bad?

326
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,320
Who doesn't have feelings for this factory?

327
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,360
You think I want to leave?

328
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:36,400
But what can I do?

329
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:36,840
Yeah.

330
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,400
Say I stay out of loyalty.

331
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:39,320
I stay.

332
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,520
Then what?

333
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:42,360
How do I live after that?

334
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,120
Master hasn't spoken yet.

335
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:45,920
Let's just focus on our own work first.

336
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:23,840
What I mean is,

337
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,440
we don't have to give them shares.

338
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:28,120
Dayazhai has no obligation to, after all.

339
00:15:28,760 --> 00:15:29,600
But,

340
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:32,360
we can send some orders their way.

341
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:34,480
Think of it as helping fellow tradesmen.

342
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:38,120
Let me be honest with you, Xuan Yan.

343
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:39,880
Right now, the group

344
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:42,160
is very optimistic about cultural products.

345
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,640
And we've already made our moves.

346
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:45,680
Around Taohua Town,

347
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:48,360
we're building our own supply chain.

348
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:50,120
As for Dayazhai's production standards,

349
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:51,000
you know them well.

350
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:54,280
High-quality, low-cost production

351
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:55,760
took us so many years

352
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:57,120
to perfect.

353
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,840
If you now hand orders over to them,

354
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,240
that means our costs go up.

355
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,280
Another thing,

356
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:06,720
quality control becomes hard to guarantee.

357
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:12,760
Quality can be managed by contracts, systems,

358
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:14,000
and oversight, right?

359
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,960
As for the costs,

360
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,360
I'll follow Dayazhai's requirements

361
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:19,680
and keep them as low as I can.

362
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,280
So the way you're putting it,

363
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:26,360
I have no choice but to accept?

364
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:27,520
It's just a suggestion.

365
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:31,480
Fine.

366
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:32,960
Then give me a reason

367
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:35,080
that I can convince myself with.

368
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:45,440
Just think of it

369
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:48,200
as doing me a favor.

370
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,160
I'm from here.

371
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:55,120
I want the people here to prosper.

372
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:56,720
And I also hope

373
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,760
that Taohua Town keeps thriving.

374
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:02,600
This kind of feeling,

375
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:07,000
you should be able to understand, right?

376
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:10,800
Like your father's feelings for traditional Xuan paper.

377
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:17,480
I've noticed something.

378
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:19,400
You people from Taohua Town,

379
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:20,920
you love bringing sentiment into business.

380
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:23,040
You don't think in business terms.

381
00:17:23,359 --> 00:17:25,000
You don't weigh pros and cons.

382
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:28,280
Having one like Xiao Min is one thing.

383
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:29,840
But how can even someone like you,

384
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,760
a well-educated, sharp young man,

385
00:17:31,760 --> 00:17:32,840
fall for the same thing?

386
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:38,200
Maybe it's a leftover from agrarian culture,

387
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,600
that attachment to one's homeland.

388
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,480
It's our nostalgia.

389
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,080
You can talk to me about nostalgia,

390
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,600
but what do I tell the chairman?

391
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:50,320
You're just making things hard for me.

392
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:01,280
Who's there?

393
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,600
Yongnian.

394
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:05,400
Are you asleep?

395
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:09,480
Laoke.

396
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:10,720
Yongnian.

397
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:11,520
What's wrong?

398
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:16,160
I've got this nagging feeling something's up.

399
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:19,240
I couldn't stay in bed.

400
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:21,000
In all these years,

401
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:23,400
this is the first time I've felt so uneasy.

402
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:25,560
Heart racing?

403
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:28,640
Come, come.

404
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:30,640
Let me listen.

405
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:32,720
It's not that.

406
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:35,200
Then what is it?

407
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:39,280
Did you see something,

408
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:40,240
or hear something?

409
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,720
I wish I could hear something.

410
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:45,400
The folks at the mill these days,

411
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:47,000
they talk behind my back.

412
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:49,000
They're starting to keep secrets from me.

413
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,480
Good things aren't hidden from people.

414
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:53,080
What's hidden is never good.

415
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:56,240
So I wanted to warn you and Xuan Yan.

416
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:59,000
We've got to prepare for the worst.

417
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:05,680
Don't get too worked up.

418
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:08,600
They've been with us for decades.

419
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:10,440
We know them inside out.

420
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:13,240
Yes, we know them well.

421
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:14,200
But,

422
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,280
take what Sulan said, for instance.

423
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:19,160
She doesn't want to take money for nothing.

424
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:21,160
She wants to earn her keep with skill.

425
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:22,960
Is there anything wrong with that?

426
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:24,840
But then again,

427
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:27,000
if everyone thinks like her,

428
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,400
I shouldn't say this, but,

429
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:31,240
if they all up and leave,

430
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:32,840
would the Xuan family still be the Xuan family?

431
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:39,480
Of course,

432
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:42,520
if all the Xuan people left,

433
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,000
and no one made paper anymore,

434
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:48,920
then it wouldn't be the Xuan family.

435
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,000
That's the truth.

436
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,360
The Xuan family, all these years,

437
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,720
has relied on them.

438
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:56,800
They are the roots of the Xuan family.

439
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:58,800
Yongnian,

440
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,520
no matter what,

441
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,320
we can't let them leave.

442
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:06,800
This matter,

443
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,720
we need to think it over carefully.

444
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:11,600
Give it some thought.

445
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:13,680
We can't afford the slightest mistake.

446
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:15,160
Here's what we'll do.

447
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:17,440
I'll go talk to Xuan Yan again,

448
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,080
and have a good talk with him.

449
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:22,400
As for you,

450
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:28,080
just set your mind at ease.

451
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:44,680
It's so late.

452
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:46,680
What did Laoke want to talk about?

453
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:50,280
Laoke?

454
00:20:52,560 --> 00:20:54,480
He's afraid the Xuan family will fall apart.

455
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:56,760
Would it, though?

456
00:20:58,320 --> 00:20:59,200
Well, this whole thing...

457
00:21:01,320 --> 00:21:04,000
Xuan Yan handles things too recklessly.

458
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:06,800
He means well.

459
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:09,920
He's thinking of our family's long-term future.

460
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:11,680
The whole thing's about to fall apart.

461
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:14,240
What long-term future is there to talk about?

462
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:19,840
He's young.

463
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:22,720
It's easy to blurt something out.

464
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:24,200
But taking it back...

465
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:26,120
That's a whole lot harder.

466
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:28,720
You can't blame him.

467
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,520
Then who am I supposed to blame?

468
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:32,240
You? Or me?

469
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:35,920
There you go being unreasonable again.

470
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:37,200
I'm done talking to you.

471
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:45,000
Fine.

472
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:47,160
Not talking to me again.

473
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:50,760
Suit yourself, then.

474
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:00,520
Boss Xiao,

475
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:01,560
since you're here right now,

476
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:02,720
there's something I need to tell you.

477
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:03,920
Go ahead, Master Xia.

478
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:06,560
Someone from the Xuan family wants to come work here.

479
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:07,480
Who?

480
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:09,000
He asked me not to say.

481
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:10,960
He just asked me to inquire.

482
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:13,240
The Xuans are switching product lines.

483
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:15,480
They don't need as many workers now.

484
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:18,760
The Xuans are switching.

485
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:19,920
I know about that.

486
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,200
Everyone in town

487
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:22,800
is talking about it.

488
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:25,080
But the Xuans

489
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,280
haven't mentioned laying anyone off.

490
00:22:27,320 --> 00:22:28,280
Even if they don't fire people,

491
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:30,040
folks can still choose to leave, right?

492
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:31,120
Look,

493
00:22:31,120 --> 00:22:33,240
he isn't making any money at the Xuans' now,

494
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,600
so there's no point staying.

495
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:36,280
So this matter, what do you say?

496
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:39,600
We can't get involved in this.

497
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:43,160
Here's what we'll do, Master Xia.

498
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:45,960
You just go and tell

499
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:47,000
that person who asked you,

500
00:22:47,120 --> 00:22:48,040
our temple is too small

501
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:49,520
to house such a great deity.

502
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:50,760
Tell them to seek better opportunities elsewhere.

503
00:22:50,760 --> 00:22:51,360
Alright.

504
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:52,240
Okay, okay, okay.

505
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:53,520
I'll pass on your message.

506
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:54,160
Good.

507
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:58,000
Master Chen,

508
00:22:58,320 --> 00:23:00,520
eat, drink and sleep as you please on the way.

509
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:01,880
But one rule:

510
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,120
not a drop of alcohol.

511
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:04,640
Alright, get going.

512
00:23:04,840 --> 00:23:05,680
Don't worry, Boss Xiao.

513
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:06,080
Good.

514
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:12,240
Have a safe trip.

515
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:13,080
Balance work and rest.

516
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:14,560
Got it. Don't worry, Boss Xiao.

517
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:19,200
At our current production capacity,

518
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:21,120
meeting market demand is no problem.

519
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:24,200
The key issue is after the new products launch.

520
00:23:25,360 --> 00:23:27,480
For a single product, we can barely manage.

521
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:29,080
But with multiple products,

522
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:30,800
things get really tight.

523
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:32,000
No worries.

524
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,040
I'll coordinate when the time comes.

525
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:33,960
Alright.

526
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:36,280
When our new products launch,

527
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:37,320
and how many we can roll out,

528
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:39,360
depends on our great designer Xuan.

529
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:41,200
Just rest assured.

530
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,600
I won't keep you waiting too long.

531
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:44,040
After all, I also want our factory

532
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:45,040
to earn a bit more money,

533
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:47,560
so I can give the workers bigger bonuses,

534
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:49,720
and stop them from griping about scooping paper.

535
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:52,240
By the way,

536
00:23:52,560 --> 00:23:53,800
I heard that

537
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:56,160
your factory's transition isn't going smoothly.

538
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:58,280
If you ask me,

539
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,120
there are no secrets in Taohua Town.

540
00:24:00,120 --> 00:24:01,280
You have no idea.

541
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,480
First thing this morning,

542
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:03,800
my dad started calling me nonstop.

543
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:05,280
Buzz, buzz, buzz,

544
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:06,480
buzzing till my little head

545
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:08,520
grew bigger than both of yours combined.

546
00:24:08,560 --> 00:24:09,360
Understandable.

547
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:12,160
Reform always comes with growing pains.

548
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:14,320
Boss Xuan,

549
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:15,400
your father is here.

550
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:16,720
You'd better go check on him.

551
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:18,400
He looks like he's ready to pick a fight.

552
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,280
So the pain kicks in just like that?

553
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:24,680
Where's my dad?

554
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:25,480
Over there.

555
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:30,560
Oh my...

556
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:31,960
Oh, my dear father!

557
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:33,720
What are you doing here?

558
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:35,920
Boss Xuan.

559
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:37,000
Boss Xuan, hello.

560
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:40,400
Boss Xuan, please come this way.

561
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:41,720
Let me make you some tea.

562
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:43,000
We can chat over tea.

563
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,280
Thanks, I've got my own tea.

564
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:47,360
You don't come home,

565
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,680
you don't answer calls.

566
00:24:50,520 --> 00:24:51,920
I've been busy, haven't I?

567
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:53,840
Can't we discuss urgent matters at home?

568
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:56,240
I didn't sleep well all last night.

569
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,560
Your Uncle Laoke

570
00:24:58,680 --> 00:24:59,840
didn't sleep either.

571
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:04,000
He told me you want to split off people for cultural products.

572
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:06,920
He said it can't be done.

573
00:25:07,200 --> 00:25:08,480
And he also said

574
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:10,480
that because of this,

575
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:12,600
the Xuan family might fall apart.

576
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:21,080
You two,

577
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:23,200
worrying less would be the best thing.

578
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:24,520
The meeting hasn't even happened yet.

579
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,280
For something this big,

580
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,920
you'd better think it through thoroughly.

581
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:32,520
Have you considered the worst-case scenario?

582
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:33,920
Let me ask you,

583
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:34,920
when you hold the meeting,

584
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:37,560
if everyone refuses to do cultural products,

585
00:25:38,760 --> 00:25:39,720
what will you do?

586
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:41,120
Then I'll handpick people.

587
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:43,760
I'll have Uncle Ye, Auntie Sulan, and Magan

588
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,080
do cultural products with me.

589
00:25:45,080 --> 00:25:46,360
I won't move anyone else.

590
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:49,960
Why arrange it this way?

591
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:52,120
You need to think it through.

592
00:25:52,360 --> 00:25:53,920
Give me a proper reason.

593
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,080
You're the boss now.

594
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,600
When you speak and act,

595
00:25:57,600 --> 00:26:00,520
you have to convince everyone completely.

596
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:03,240
Boss Xuan,

597
00:26:03,280 --> 00:26:04,320
please don't get worked up.

598
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:05,280
I believe in Xuan Yan.

599
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:06,640
He has a way to handle this.

600
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:15,680
Dad.

601
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:17,480
How about this?

602
00:26:17,520 --> 00:26:18,960
Those who join my cultural creative team,

603
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:20,000
not only will their pay not be cut,

604
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,960
I'll give each of them an extra 500 yuan bonus.

605
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:24,080
Xiao Yu cares about money more than anything.

606
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:25,120
You know that.

607
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:27,000
Why wouldn't he come for the money?

608
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:31,480
From Uncle Ye's and Uncle Hu's families,

609
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:33,360
we'll take one person from each.

610
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:35,600
Auntie Sulan works fast

611
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:36,520
and doesn't argue.

612
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:37,720
If Mom has a good talk with her,

613
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:38,960
she'll definitely come.

614
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:39,840
And also,

615
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,560
with Magan and Uncle Ye,

616
00:26:41,560 --> 00:26:42,840
it's the same reasoning.

617
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:45,200
Isn't this fair and reasonable?

618
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:47,840
This is all your own thinking.

619
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,840
Let's not even talk about Xiao Yu.

620
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:53,240
Sulan and her husband,

621
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:55,720
they're master paper dryers.

622
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:56,160
Yes.

623
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:58,680
Their craft and skill are top-notch.

624
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:00,520
And the two of them have worked together

625
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:01,680
for how long now?

626
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:03,720
Longer than you've been alive.

627
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:04,240
Yes, yes, yes.

628
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:06,040
What gives you the right to split them up

629
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:07,600
and pull one away for cultural creations?

630
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:09,920
And then there's Magan.

631
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:12,760
You want Magan to work on cultural creations?

632
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:14,160
Can he even handle it?

633
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:15,280
With that nasty temper of his,

634
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:17,280
once he digs in, could you sway him?

635
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:20,480
Old Ye wants Magan

636
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:24,040
to master a solid paper-scooping skill,

637
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:26,960
so he has something to rely on later in life.

638
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:28,880
Even if we set all that aside,

639
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:31,760
even if Magan went with you for cultural work,

640
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,480
would Old Ye agree to it?

641
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:36,960
He wouldn't allow it.

642
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:40,000
Dad.

643
00:27:40,560 --> 00:27:41,720
I really don't know what to do with you.

644
00:27:43,320 --> 00:27:44,440
Nothing's even been decided yet.

645
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:46,200
Can we stop guessing wildly?

646
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:46,800
What?

647
00:27:49,520 --> 00:27:50,760
Am I guessing?

648
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:53,160
How long have I worked

649
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:55,000
alongside these people?

650
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:56,120
Do I need to guess?

651
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:59,000
This is huge for the Xuan family.

652
00:27:59,160 --> 00:28:00,960
One wrong step ruins everything.

653
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:04,120
You've taken on the Xuan family's burden now.

654
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:05,560
Every single matter,

655
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:08,000
you need to think through clearly.

656
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:10,360
Let me make this clear again.

657
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:13,920
You should be having sleepless nights right now.

658
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:15,920
Sleepless or not,

659
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,480
this thing still has to be done, right?

660
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:18,800
Fine, let's not waste words.

661
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,120
I'll just ask you one thing.

662
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:24,920
If everyone doesn't do as you expect,

663
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:26,960
when you make arrangements,

664
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:29,960
and they refuse to work on cultural creations,

665
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:32,120
what will you do?

666
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:33,080
Then I...

667
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:50,760
Boss Xuan, may I chime in?

668
00:28:51,040 --> 00:28:51,840
You see,

669
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:54,040
a household of thousands still needs one leader.

670
00:28:54,120 --> 00:28:56,680
Whether a company is big or small,

671
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:58,160
it must have rules and regulations.

672
00:28:58,320 --> 00:29:00,080
Once the boss has arranged something,

673
00:29:00,080 --> 00:29:01,680
employees must obey.

674
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:02,720
If they don't obey,

675
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:03,840
then I'm sorry to say,

676
00:29:03,840 --> 00:29:05,080
they have to be fired.

677
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:07,320
The Xuan family has no such policy.

678
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,120
Quitting or firing,

679
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,200
not allowed.

680
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:15,160
I see, I see.

681
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:17,120
But for a business to grow,

682
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:19,720
it has to rely on rules and regulations.

683
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:21,680
Look, take our Dayazhai for example,

684
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:23,280
a corporate group

685
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:24,920
with so many people under it.

686
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,360
If we didn't rely on rules

687
00:29:26,360 --> 00:29:26,920
to keep everyone in check...

688
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:29,280
When your Dayazhai reaches a thousand years,

689
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,760
then come tell me this.

690
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:38,880
Xuan Yan.

691
00:29:39,160 --> 00:29:41,040
You need to take what I said today to heart.

692
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:42,480
You must think twice before acting.

693
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:48,920
I...

694
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:51,160
Quick, quick, see him out.

695
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:53,000
Boss Xuan, take care.

696
00:29:53,080 --> 00:29:54,000
Let me walk you out.

697
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:08,440
Xuan Yan.

698
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:10,320
Actually,

699
00:30:10,560 --> 00:30:11,720
with a temper like his,

700
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:12,960
you see...

701
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:14,760
It's fine.

702
00:30:15,320 --> 00:30:16,200
I understand.

703
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:20,040
That's the tough part of family business reform.

704
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:22,680
Too many rules, too much baggage.

705
00:30:23,480 --> 00:30:24,800
Our family matters

706
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:26,600
are tough to handle.

707
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:29,240
But my dad's right.

708
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:31,000
On this matter,

709
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,480
we still need to think it through more.

710
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:33,800
Consider it more carefully.

711
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:37,480
But I have to remind you,

712
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:39,720
without rules, nothing gets done.

713
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:42,600
I'm just puzzled.

714
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:44,960
It's just letting a few people go.

715
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:46,240
Is it really that difficult?

716
00:30:47,600 --> 00:30:48,600
You just don't get it.

717
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,280
Our family's more than just a small business,

718
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:53,000
it's really one big family.

719
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:57,240
Alright, let's drop the subject.

720
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,200
Right now,

721
00:30:58,200 --> 00:31:00,720
I'm looking forward to your new works soon.

722
00:31:01,240 --> 00:31:02,440
Take this cultural-creative path

723
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:03,640
and make it big and strong.

724
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:14,480
Hold on, hold on.

725
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:17,200
Have you all thought it through yet?

726
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,360
Every meal, nobody talks.

727
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:20,960
Feels like a funeral.

728
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:23,960
What do you think?

729
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:25,640
I'll say it again:

730
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,280
we make a living by our craft.

731
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:28,640
We don't take other people's money for nothing.

732
00:31:29,840 --> 00:31:30,480
Exactly.

733
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:32,080
Take these creative products,

734
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:33,120
which of you has ever done that?

735
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:34,680
If we can't do it well,

736
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,160
taking so much money from others

737
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:37,960
just doesn't sit right.

738
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:39,280
That's what I mean.

739
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:41,520
The thing is, the old Xuan family

740
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:43,400
has no tradition of firing workers.

741
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:45,000
If you try to let them go,

742
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:46,480
old Xuan definitely won't agree.

743
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:47,680
If you force it,

744
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:50,640
it'll hurt those bonds we have.

745
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:52,400
I don't see it that way.

746
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:53,920
If you don't speak up honestly,

747
00:31:54,040 --> 00:31:55,680
that's what really hurts the bond.

748
00:31:57,480 --> 00:31:58,280
Why aren't they here yet?

749
00:31:59,160 --> 00:32:00,040
What's going on with you?

750
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:01,240
Why aren't you coming in?

751
00:32:01,240 --> 00:32:02,280
Everyone's waiting.

752
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,280
Not even eager to eat.

753
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:03,840
Hurry, hurry.

754
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:04,840
Coming, coming.

755
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:05,480
Let's go.

756
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:06,240
Let's eat first, eat.

757
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:09,800
Dad.

758
00:32:13,240 --> 00:32:14,600
So, what do we do?

759
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:19,480
Just focus on eating for now.

760
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:21,360
Say less, let them talk.

761
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,520
Everyone, dig in.

762
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:56,040
Hurry up and eat.

763
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:57,080
You've all had a long day.

764
00:32:57,360 --> 00:32:58,840
Here, I brought a bottle too.

765
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:00,240
Old Ye, come on.

766
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:02,000
Have a drink to unwind tonight.

767
00:33:03,200 --> 00:33:04,680
Drink up.

768
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,200
Alright.

769
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:05,760
Here.

770
00:33:05,760 --> 00:33:06,240
Come on, come on.

771
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:07,080
Alright, alright.

772
00:33:07,840 --> 00:33:09,000
Have a bit if you feel like it.

773
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:10,080
Pour some, pour some.

774
00:33:10,520 --> 00:33:11,200
Not drinking?

775
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:13,160
I haven't touched it. Switch seats.

776
00:33:14,360 --> 00:33:15,160
Go on.

777
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:16,200
Let me pour you one too.

778
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:17,200
Go on, I haven't touched it.

779
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:18,600
Hurry up.

780
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:21,680
Xiao Yu.

781
00:33:22,280 --> 00:33:24,160
By the rules of Taohua Town,

782
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:26,520
master craftsmen don't sit by rank at meals.

783
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:28,840
You taking the lower seat like this,

784
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:30,920
that means you're quitting.

785
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:35,000
Well, since there's a rule,

786
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:36,240
let's just go by the rule.

787
00:33:37,560 --> 00:33:39,520
Brother, do me a favor.

788
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:45,000
Today, I...

789
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:46,640
No way.

790
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:51,200
Xiaoman.

791
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:53,880
Not today either.

792
00:34:00,280 --> 00:34:01,080
Master,

793
00:34:03,320 --> 00:34:04,160
Mistress,

794
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:05,840
my dad has retired.

795
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:08,239
He says I should return to the Hongxing mill.

796
00:34:16,520 --> 00:34:17,239
Look,

797
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:20,760
Xiaoman came to the Xuan family to learn the craft.

798
00:34:21,040 --> 00:34:22,520
It's been many years.

799
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:24,239
It's time he finished his apprenticeship.

800
00:34:24,239 --> 00:34:24,719
Yes, yes.

801
00:34:24,719 --> 00:34:25,480
Right?

802
00:34:26,239 --> 00:34:27,080
My dad said

803
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:28,960
he'd bring me here another day

804
00:34:29,239 --> 00:34:30,719
to bow to Master and Mistress,

805
00:34:31,040 --> 00:34:32,440
and throw a proper thank-you banquet.

806
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:35,520
Thank your father for me.

807
00:34:36,639 --> 00:34:38,239
I got it. Sit down.

808
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:49,040
Master Yu,

809
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:52,719
you've been with the Xuan family

810
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:54,239
not as long as the others,

811
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:57,000
but still a good ten years.

812
00:34:58,040 --> 00:34:59,000
The Xuan family

813
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:00,840
has its old rules.

814
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:04,320
If it's about your wages being too low,

815
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:06,320
we can raise them gradually.

816
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:08,160
That can be worked out.

817
00:35:08,280 --> 00:35:09,080
Right, right.

818
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:10,160
Xiao Yu,

819
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:11,680
is it because you've seen

820
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,280
that the Xuan business isn't doing well lately?

821
00:35:14,160 --> 00:35:15,320
All these years,

822
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:17,240
no matter how bad business got,

823
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:20,040
Brother's never shorted anyone's pay.

824
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:21,680
No.

825
00:35:22,560 --> 00:35:23,680
So in your eyes,

826
00:35:23,680 --> 00:35:25,360
I'm just money-hungry?

827
00:35:26,240 --> 00:35:27,200
If it's not for the money,

828
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:28,520
then what's it for?

829
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:35,000
Money.

830
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:39,320
Yes, it's for the money.

831
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:41,520
Okay?

832
00:35:42,400 --> 00:35:43,320
Master, I'm sorry.

833
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:47,840
My mom is sick.

834
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:50,640
So I can't worry about it.

835
00:35:51,080 --> 00:35:52,120
I can't afford to.

836
00:35:52,120 --> 00:35:52,920
As for me,

837
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:55,640
wherever pays more,

838
00:35:56,640 --> 00:35:57,720
that's where I'll go.

839
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:02,680
Right? Besides, look,

840
00:36:02,680 --> 00:36:04,320
the way things are at the Xuan mill now,

841
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:07,680
you don't need two vats for scooping paper.

842
00:36:08,280 --> 00:36:09,760
For drying, the couple's got it covered.

843
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:10,680
They can handle it, right?

844
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:16,240
Yeah.

845
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:19,640
Ten years.

846
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:24,320
I owe the Xuan family too much.

847
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:26,920
I don't want to owe more.

848
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:30,920
I've said all I can say.

849
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:31,520
So,

850
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:33,480
please don't make this harder for me.

851
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:35,040
Let's all just enjoy the meal, alright?

852
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,000
Yongnian.

853
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:51,080
You can't force these things.

854
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:53,320
Just let him be.

855
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:01,480
What's going on between you two,

856
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:03,520
I understand it all.

857
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:06,520
Today, let's just enjoy the meal.

858
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:07,600
Also,

859
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:09,400
the Mid-Autumn Festival is in a few days.

860
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:10,840
I hope,

861
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:14,360
no matter where you all are,

862
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:17,120
you'll come back for the festival.

863
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:19,400
So that all of us

864
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,520
can have a proper reunion.

865
00:37:21,560 --> 00:37:22,360
All right?

866
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:25,200
Let's eat.

867
00:37:25,520 --> 00:37:26,400
Come on, come on.

868
00:37:27,040 --> 00:37:27,880
Old Ye.

869
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:29,760
Old Hu.

870
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,080
Come, have some wine.

871
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:34,640
Xiao Yu.

872
00:37:36,480 --> 00:37:37,400
Eat first.

873
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:46,040
Let's eat first.

874
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:09,040
So you two are hiding out here.

875
00:38:10,600 --> 00:38:12,520
The doctor told you to rest more.

876
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:13,400
Get some proper rest.

877
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:14,640
But you just won't listen, will you?

878
00:38:16,520 --> 00:38:17,480
I'm worried.

879
00:38:21,080 --> 00:38:21,840
Xiaoman...

880
00:38:22,520 --> 00:38:24,360
It's time for him to go anyway.

881
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:25,920
And Xiao Yu too.

882
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:27,520
It's just as well they're leaving.

883
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:29,360
It won't hold anything up.

884
00:38:29,640 --> 00:38:30,440
Just now,

885
00:38:30,760 --> 00:38:32,320
I worked it out with Xiumei.

886
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:33,040
From now on,

887
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:35,520
Master Ye and Magan will scoop the paper.

888
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:38,160
Sulan and I will dry it together.

889
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:40,520
As for Master Hu,

890
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:41,880
he's a strong one.

891
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:45,760
He'll mix the pulp and do creative products.

892
00:38:46,360 --> 00:38:48,160
Everything's going to work out fine.

893
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:50,360
It's still the old Xuan family.

894
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:53,160
Blessed by our ancestors, richly favored.

895
00:38:53,640 --> 00:38:56,360
Heaven has arranged it all for you.

896
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:02,400
I just don't know

897
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:04,960
if Xiao Hu will be willing to do it.

898
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:06,560
Sulan will handle it.

899
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:08,440
I'll go find her later

900
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:10,520
and have a proper talk with her.

901
00:39:10,720 --> 00:39:11,800
I know.

902
00:39:12,040 --> 00:39:14,360
Sulan may have a sharp tongue,

903
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:17,080
but she's the most reasonable one of all.

904
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:19,840
That's true.

905
00:39:23,720 --> 00:39:24,520
Sulan,

906
00:39:25,720 --> 00:39:27,720
when you and your husband came to the Xuan family,

907
00:39:28,560 --> 00:39:31,120
I was still holding Xuan Yan in my arms.

908
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:34,400
So many years have passed in the blink of an eye.

909
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:38,240
Never mind how the Xuans have treated you two,

910
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:40,360
but how you two have treated the Xuans,

911
00:39:40,360 --> 00:39:42,040
I know very well in my heart.

912
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:46,680
Old Hu is a skilled craftsman.

913
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:49,360
We have never looked down on him.

914
00:39:50,080 --> 00:39:51,120
But this time,

915
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:54,120
we really have no other choice.

916
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:56,640
We'll have to ask him to bear with it.

917
00:39:59,640 --> 00:40:00,440
Sis,

918
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:04,400
you're really putting me in a tough spot.

919
00:40:04,400 --> 00:40:05,040
I know.

920
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:06,520
With skills like you two have,

921
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:07,640
no matter whose family you went to,

922
00:40:07,640 --> 00:40:09,480
they'd burn incense and worship you.

923
00:40:09,840 --> 00:40:10,840
But Sulan,

924
00:40:13,640 --> 00:40:16,880
we're truly in a bind.

925
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:19,640
There's just no other way.

926
00:40:26,240 --> 00:40:27,320
I know, sis.

927
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:30,360
If the two of us left now,

928
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:33,080
who would dry the paper for our family?

929
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:38,000
Sulan,

930
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:42,040
all these years you've been with the Xuans,

931
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:44,360
I've treated you like my own little sister.

932
00:40:44,480 --> 00:40:45,320
And you know

933
00:40:45,320 --> 00:40:47,080
I've never asked you for anything.

934
00:40:47,080 --> 00:40:47,960
Isn't that right?

935
00:40:48,040 --> 00:40:48,560
Sis...

936
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:49,840
Today,

937
00:40:50,600 --> 00:40:52,120
on behalf of the Xuan family,

938
00:40:52,960 --> 00:40:54,200
I'm begging you.

939
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:57,560
This kindness,

940
00:40:57,640 --> 00:40:59,920
I'll definitely repay you someday.

941
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:01,640
You know,

942
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:05,360
the Xuans have never wronged anyone.

943
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:15,000
Alright.

944
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:16,520
Alright, sis.

945
00:41:16,840 --> 00:41:18,440
Set your mind at ease.

946
00:41:18,840 --> 00:41:20,040
I'll go talk to Old Hu.

947
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:21,520
You go on with your work.

948
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:22,840
I'm going right now.

949
00:41:39,040 --> 00:41:40,880
What were you and Xiumei talking about outside?

950
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:41,920
Chattering forever.

951
00:41:43,280 --> 00:41:44,200
Nothing much.

952
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:48,080
In a couple of days, go help pulp the paper.

953
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:51,440
Then work on those creative products.

954
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:55,840
I knew you were a soft touch.

955
00:41:55,880 --> 00:41:57,640
The moment someone sweet-talks you,

956
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:59,040
you forget who you are.

957
00:41:59,040 --> 00:41:59,720
Right?

958
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:03,960
The Xuan family's in a tough spot now.

959
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:05,520
If we leave at a time like this,

960
00:42:05,520 --> 00:42:06,920
the paper won't get dried.

961
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:09,560
So you're punishing me with pulping?

962
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:11,920
I, Hu Wanjin, in Taohua Town,

963
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:14,080
am a master craftsman wherever I go.

964
00:42:14,080 --> 00:42:15,160
Master craftsman, master craftsman.

965
00:42:15,160 --> 00:42:16,880
Have you brought home mountains of gold?

966
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:19,040
As long as they don't shortchange you, it's fine.

967
00:42:20,600 --> 00:42:22,240
Why didn't she ask someone else?

968
00:42:22,480 --> 00:42:24,520
Because she respects you, Hu Wanjin.

969
00:42:25,360 --> 00:42:26,560
Oh, so that's respect?

970
00:42:27,120 --> 00:42:29,040
Has your brain gone bad?

971
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:31,360
Your husband dries paper.

972
00:42:31,360 --> 00:42:32,960
I'm a paper-drying master!

973
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:34,400
If I do creative products for a few years,

974
00:42:34,400 --> 00:42:35,160
then afterwards,

975
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:36,800
who'll remember I'm a paper-drying master?

976
00:42:37,120 --> 00:42:39,000
I already promised Sister Xiumei.

977
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:40,360
You can't back out.

978
00:42:43,120 --> 00:42:43,880
You...

979
00:42:44,560 --> 00:42:45,520
One of these days,

980
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:46,840
I'll finally be driven

981
00:42:46,840 --> 00:42:48,360
to death by you, woman!

982
00:42:49,760 --> 00:42:50,640
Where are you going?

983
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:52,080
Old Hu!

984
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:53,360
Get back here!

985
00:42:53,520 --> 00:42:54,440
Old Hu!
